<p style="text-align: left;">This is the Girl Up Amity blog! Click the title of this post to read more.</p><p>In order to make a new post, go to&nbsp;<a href="http://girlup.github.io/cms">the admin page.</a>&nbsp;You need to insert a post title and a post body. You will find that you can do some cool stuff in there, like <b>bold</b>&nbsp;or <u>underline</u>&nbsp;text, <font face="Courier New">different fonts</font><font face="Arial">,</font></p><ul><li><font face="Arial">Bulleted</font></li><li><font face="Arial">Lists,</font></li></ul><p style="text-align: center; "><font face="Arial">Centered or</font></p><p style="text-align: right;"><font face="Arial">Right aligned text,</font></p><p style="text-align: left;"><font face="Arial"><br></font></p><table class="table table-bordered"><tbody><tr><td>Tables,</td><td><br></td></tr><tr><td><br></td><td><br></td></tr></tbody></table><h1 style="text-align: left;"><font face="Arial">Headers,</font></h1><p style="text-align: left;"><font face="Arial" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);">highlighted</font><font face="Arial">&nbsp;or <font color="#9c00ff">colored text,</font></font></p><blockquote style="text-align: left;"><p><font face="Arial">blockquotes,</font></p></blockquote><p><br></p><p style="text-align: left;">and you can even copy/paste or drag/drop images or embed youtube videos!</p><p style="text-align: left;"><img src="data:image/png;base64," data-filename="girlupamity.png" style="width: 111.492px; height: 91px;"></p><p style="text-align: left;"><br></p><p style="text-align: left;">You can also choose to show an alternate blurb on the homepage for your post (by default it just shows the first paragraph). You can also choose to center the preview "card" on the homepage (by default they will align in 2 columns on desktop and 1 column on mobile).</p><p style="text-align: left;">Be aware, you can't just press enter to submit the post because of the way the form is made (I might be able to change that, idk). You have to click Post for it to work.</p><p style="text-align: left;">Notice how there is a Disqus comments section below this post. Anyone can comment as long as they sign in with their Facebook, Twitter, Google (school emails might work), or Disqus account. You can also moderate comments if you are logged in as a Disqus moderator.</p><p style="text-align: left;"><br></p><p style="text-align: left;">Update: you can now edit and delete posts on the admin page. Just go to the post you want to edit, copy the hashtag and everything after it in the address bar, then paste it after the address in the admin page. In order to delete a post, leave the title blank and click Post.&nbsp;</p><p style="text-align: left;">I also added support to link directly to another blog post. Doing this makes it so that I can show the slide animation between posts and make the back button work nicer since you are actually staying on one page. Just copy the address of the post you want to link to and click the permalink button on the toolbar (it's the diagonal chain link).&nbsp;</p>
